n. The present volume also contains draft legislation, fascinating case notes from his legal practice, and personal correspondence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aDelaware, Pennsylvania, John Dickinson, Dickinson, legal, Philadelphia, Quaker, Kent County, legislator, leadership, Moland, eighteenth century, Britain, Great Britain, England, British, British Empire, Mary Cadwalader Dickinson, Israel Pemberton, William Allason, George Read, Thomas McKean, John Moland, military, poem, writing, Pennsylvania Assembly, Delaware assembly, verse, books, legislation, 1759, 1763, Benjamin Franklin, Society of Friends.1 aCalvert, Jane E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalvert, Jane E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978164453274440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781644532744423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781644532744/original  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles